20/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov wrapped up a two-day visit to neighbouring Macedonia Saturday (19 June). He was there at the invitation of his Macedonian counterpart, Branko Crvenkovski.Parvanov lauded the excellent bilateral relations between the two countries and reiterated Bulgaria's full support for Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic integration efforts.
In other news, a ceremony at the Bulgarian Interior Ministry on Friday (18 June) marked the opening of an FBI office in Sofia. In attendance were Interior Ministry Chief Secretary Boyko Borisov, US Ambassador to Bulgaria James Pardew and FBI legal attach√© in Athens Robert Clifford.The office will be involved in the fight against organised crime and terrorism, and will work with Bulgarian authorities as they seek to root out judicial corruption. (Makfax, A1 TV, news.bg, Sega - 19/06/04; Mediapool - 18/06/04)
